Column Comment.0: FOSSIL IDENTIFIER: Unique Identifier for a fossil.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: CLIMATE: a type of environmental climate that existed in past or exists today.Examples include tropical, arctic, tundra or arid.
Column Comment.3: EFFECTIVE DATE: date on which the data in this row came into effect.
Column Comment.4: EXPIRY DATE: Date on which the data in this row of data was no longer in effect.
Column Comment.5: FOSSIL LIFE HABIT: The life habit of the fossil, or where it typically is found duringlife, such as benthic, planctonic etc.
Column Comment.6: ECOZONE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a sedimentary rock unit or environmentin which fossil deposition occurs. Often, these ecozones are marine or fresh water.Marine ecozones include the category of marine benthic zones, namely shelf, slope,and abyssal zones. The ecozone is defined by the organisms that are found in it.
Column Comment.7: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.8: PREFERRED INDICATOR: A Y / N flag indicating whether this fossil is part of thepreferred set of fossils. By default, these fossils should be used for most queries andreports.
Column Comment.9: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.10: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.11: FOSSILTAXONOMIC GROUP: The taxonomic group that has been assigned to afossil. Fossils may belong to a genus, subgenus, species or subspecies.
Column Comment.12: TAXONOMIC LEAF IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a taxonomic leaf, whichidentifies a fossil species to an identified level, such as species or genus.
Column Comment.13: ECOZONE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a sedimentary rock unit or environmentin which fossil deposition occurs. Often, these ecozones are marine or fresh water.Marine ecozones include the category of marine benthic zones, namely shelf, slope,and abyssal zones. The ecozone is defined by the organisms that are found in it.
Column Comment.14: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.15: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.16: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.17: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.18: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.19: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.20: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
